|archive-date=August 20, 2008
|url-status=dead
}}&lt;/ref&gt;

''The Sun'' was listed as a three-time victim of plagiarism when the [[The News-Sentinel|Indiana-based ''News-Sentinel'']] announced March 1, 2008 that &quot;20 of 38 guest columns .. contributed .. since 2000&quot; by Bush White House staffer [[Timothy Goeglein]] were subsequently discovered to have been plagiarized; three were attributed to original articles in ''The Sun''.&lt;ref name=NewsentNySun&gt;{{cite web
